HEADWORD: Charta
<hw>Char"ta</hw> <pr>(k⟦aum⟧r"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
leaf of paper. See <er>Chart</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Material on which instruments, books, etc., are written; parchment
or paper.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A charter or deed; a writing by which
a grant is made. See <er>Magna Charta</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chartaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
